The paper deals with a clustering method (K-Medoids) and proposes a new algorithm (MCPAM) for its efficient implementation. This falls under the broad category of machine learning and data mining, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DM (Data Mining). The paper also discusses the statistical properties of the K-Medoids algorithm, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Overall, cs.LG and cs.DM seem to be the most relevant sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.SI, and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
